
[1]leisurely

   LEIS'URELY, a. Done at leisure; not hasty; deliberate; slow; as a
   leisurely walk or march; a leisurely survey of life.

   LEIS'URELY, adv. Not in haste or hurry; slowly; at leisure;
   deliberately.

   We descended very leisurely, by friend being careful to count the
   steps.
